pypac
=====

    "We called him Tortoise because he taught us"
        --Alice's Adventures in Wonderland

pypac is a fun, interactive Pac-Man environment to help teach basic programming
in Python. It makes use of the interactive Python prompt, so that learning to
use it is learning to use Python! There's no gap between pypac and "real Python
programming".

About
-----

 * Author:      David Barnett <davidbarnett2@gmail.com>
 * Home:        http://github.com/dbarnett/pypac
 * Licenses:    BSD

    Dedicated to Sara

How to use it
-------------
Execute

    python -i pypac.py
